=Description=

"We seek to develop strategic activities and projects that influence economic analysis, teaching and thinking. We look for activities the bring diverse people together and build a stronger new economics movement.

Currently our main activities are:

+ Co-creating an international accreditation system for masters courses that take a pluralist approach to economic teaching. This is aimed at building the profile of innovative teaching to influence economic teaching more broadly;
* Publishing The Mint Magazine aimed at a non-academic audience which features leading new economic thinkers and provides a range of perspectives and approaches to understand our economies; and
* Holding events to encourage discussion of the range of perspectives on different economic issues; and
* Providing consultancy services through our subsidiary New Economic Knowledge Services.

(https://economicpluralism.org/about-us/?)

